WEBVTT

00:00.567 --> 00:02.069
Previously on
"Splitting Up Together"...

00:02.069 --> 00:05.973
Lena: I had this erotic dream
about my ex-husband

00:05.973 --> 00:08.609
wherein he reached down
and unsnapped my bodysuit.

00:08.609 --> 00:10.244
Are you making
a pass at me?

00:10.244 --> 00:13.080
♪♪

00:13.080 --> 00:15.015
[ Snaps popping ]

00:15.015 --> 00:16.583
One snap left.

00:16.583 --> 00:18.819
Maybe we revisit
that third snap.

00:18.819 --> 00:22.422
♪♪

00:22.422 --> 00:23.624
[ Inhales deeply ]

00:23.624 --> 00:26.193
[ Door opens ]

00:26.193 --> 00:28.128
[ Exhales deeply ]

00:30.297 --> 00:33.834
♪♪

00:33.834 --> 00:36.637
Mm, you gonna
pack that bodysuit?

00:36.637 --> 00:38.472
Why do I
tell you anything?

00:38.472 --> 00:40.240
Do you get depressed,
every other week?

00:40.240 --> 00:42.776
When you have to leave
this really comfortable bed

00:42.776 --> 00:45.546
and go sleep in
a dusty, old garage?

00:45.546 --> 00:46.613
Are you kidding me?

00:46.613 --> 00:48.015
I am not complaining.

00:48.015 --> 00:50.217
I just got Martin back on board
with cohabiting.

00:50.217 --> 00:51.818
I am happy as a clam.

00:52.819 --> 00:55.088
But I do miss having
all my clothes in one place.

00:55.088 --> 00:58.025
And the bar from that
pull-out sofa is murder.

00:58.025 --> 00:59.660
But other than
those two things

00:59.660 --> 01:01.929
and the fact that I saw
a scorpion in there last week,

01:01.929 --> 01:04.932
the garage is
pretty much perfect.

01:04.932 --> 01:06.867
Well, perfect.

01:06.867 --> 01:09.903
I also don't love feeling
shut out of the kids' lives...

01:09.903 --> 01:10.971
Gotcha.

01:10.971 --> 01:12.673
So it's just
that excruciating back pain

01:12.673 --> 01:14.541
and being shut out
of the kids' lives,

01:14.541 --> 01:15.876
scorpions --

01:15.876 --> 01:17.411
Maybe
I am complaining.

01:17.411 --> 01:18.512
Sorry.

01:18.512 --> 01:19.813
What's new with you?

01:19.813 --> 01:21.682
Oh, thank you
for asking.

01:21.682 --> 01:23.750
I got the results back
from my amnio and --

01:23.750 --> 01:25.786
I also can hear
street traffic.
It's a boy.

01:27.154 --> 01:28.155
Oh, my gosh!

01:28.155 --> 01:30.023
Oh!
-[ Chuckles ] Mm.

01:30.023 --> 01:33.560
♪ Keep giving me hope
for a better day ♪

01:33.560 --> 01:36.697
♪ Keep giving me love
to find a way ♪

01:36.697 --> 01:39.967
♪ Through this heaviness
I feel ♪

01:39.967 --> 01:46.406
♪ I just need someone to say
everything's okay ♪

01:46.406 --> 01:47.507
♪ Everything's okay ♪

01:47.507 --> 01:49.176
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:49.176 --> 01:50.677
These are really good
with chocolate chips.

01:50.677 --> 01:52.045
Mae: Oh, we should
do that next time.

01:52.045 --> 01:53.380
'Sup, Sad Boys?

01:53.380 --> 01:54.448
What's good
in the hood?

01:54.448 --> 01:55.882
What's Gucci?

01:55.882 --> 01:58.318
China made coconut fat bombs.
Want one, Lena?

01:58.318 --> 01:59.987
Did you just
call me by my name?

01:59.987 --> 02:01.888
They're kind, raw,
and vegan.

02:01.888 --> 02:03.757
Oh, I didn't know
you were vegan, China.

02:03.757 --> 02:05.125
That's so admirable.

02:05.125 --> 02:09.129
So, to call China a "vegan"
is reductive.

02:09.129 --> 02:10.397
Reductive?

02:11.198 --> 02:12.866
It's fine.
It's just, you know --

02:12.866 --> 02:15.002
I only eat what's
granted me consent.

02:15.002 --> 02:17.304
So sometimes
I do eat animals --

02:17.304 --> 02:18.839
But only
if they're suicidal?

02:18.839 --> 02:20.273
The chicken
has to be like,

02:20.273 --> 02:22.542
[voice shaking]
"I swear to God, I'll do it!"

02:24.511 --> 02:26.813
[ Cellphone chimes ]

02:26.813 --> 02:29.082
Um, hi --
Bae watch.

02:29.082 --> 02:30.617
So bae. Way bae.

02:30.617 --> 02:32.352
[ Normal voice ]
Sittin' on the dock of the bae.

02:32.352 --> 02:35.522
I can't tell if I want her
or if I want to be her.

02:36.690 --> 02:39.026
No, I do. I want her.
[ Laughs ]

02:39.026 --> 02:41.028
I didn't realize
you were into girls.

02:42.362 --> 02:45.165
China!
That is so cool.

02:46.333 --> 02:48.568
Lena, why do you feel the need
to label everything?

02:48.568 --> 02:49.770
It's okay.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.004
She probably doesn't realize
that labels,

02:51.004 --> 02:53.607
by definition,
are attached to objects.

02:53.607 --> 02:55.809
So when you label,
you objecti--

02:55.809 --> 02:57.244
Objectify, right!

02:57.244 --> 02:59.446
Guess I've been
objectifying my spice rack

02:59.446 --> 03:00.781
all these years.

03:00.781 --> 03:02.816
Forgive me,
Cream of Tartar!

03:06.319 --> 03:08.321
No, but seriously,

03:08.321 --> 03:09.756
I get it.

03:09.756 --> 03:12.259
Okay, well, if you're
desperate for a marker,

03:12.259 --> 03:13.627
I identify as "queer."

03:13.627 --> 03:14.895
What?!
Are you kidding me?

03:14.895 --> 03:16.563
That's my favorite.

03:16.563 --> 03:18.331
"L," "G," "B," "T"
are great letters.

03:18.331 --> 03:20.267
But "Q"? Oh, my God.

03:20.267 --> 03:22.402
"Q" is the best one.

03:22.402 --> 03:24.371
Do you want
to go upstairs, Mae?
Yeah, we can, uh,

03:24.371 --> 03:26.406
do a two-person massage train
and call our senators.

03:26.406 --> 03:27.340
Uh-huh.

03:27.340 --> 03:29.176
I'll stand by "Q"!

03:29.176 --> 03:32.479
[ To the tune
of "I'll Stand by You" ]
♪ I'll stand by "Q" ♪

03:32.479 --> 03:36.316
♪ Won't let nobody hurt "Q" ♪

03:36.316 --> 03:39.252
♪ I'll stand by "Q" ♪

03:39.252 --> 03:40.687
[ Door slams in distance ]

03:40.687 --> 03:42.322
[ Sighs ]

03:42.322 --> 03:44.891
[ Quietly ]
♪ I'll stand by "Q" ♪

03:46.560 --> 03:48.795
I don't know if I'm
all the way ready for
you to leave yet.

03:48.795 --> 03:50.730
Well, that's because
you're obsessed with me.

03:50.730 --> 03:52.933
Well, that's not not true.
[ Chuckles ]

03:52.933 --> 03:54.601
Text me the second you're home?
Duh.

03:54.601 --> 03:56.303
Quick pic before you go.
Okay.

03:58.438 --> 04:00.607
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

04:00.607 --> 04:02.809
Geez, Dad. Lurk much?

04:02.809 --> 04:04.111
[ Sighs ] Same here.

04:04.111 --> 04:06.313
My parents are
full-blown stalking me.

04:06.313 --> 04:08.515
I got to go.
Okay.

04:08.515 --> 04:10.217
ILY.
ILY-SM.

04:12.552 --> 04:13.820
Hey.

04:13.820 --> 04:17.624
So, how long you guys
been official?

04:17.624 --> 04:20.794
Uh, 3 1/2 gratifying,
joy-filled weeks.

04:20.794 --> 04:23.797
Wow. And you're
already ILY'ing?

04:23.797 --> 04:25.265
Uh, privately, yeah.

04:25.265 --> 04:27.567
Bron wants to wait a few months
before we take it public

04:27.567 --> 04:29.169
so people root for us.

04:29.169 --> 04:31.471
♪♪

04:31.471 --> 04:33.507
I'm worried
about you, bud.

04:33.507 --> 04:35.208
I'm worried that you're
re-creating Hazel-gate

04:35.208 --> 04:36.776
all over again.

04:36.776 --> 04:39.880
Hazel and Bronwyn
are very different women.
Understood.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.214
But your game is the same.

04:41.214 --> 04:42.315
Listen, Mace.

04:42.315 --> 04:43.683
You're a heart-on-your-sleeve
type of guy,

04:43.683 --> 04:45.352
and that's admirable, it is.

04:45.352 --> 04:46.753
But this time,

04:46.753 --> 04:48.488
I think you need to show
a little restraint.

04:48.488 --> 04:51.158
I just can't, Dad.
I love love.

04:51.158 --> 04:54.761
And guys like me, Arthur,
Elon Musk, Kelsey Grammer --

04:54.761 --> 04:56.296
we can't live
without it.

04:57.597 --> 04:59.399
I-I appreciate that, son,

04:59.399 --> 05:02.102
but you have to leave yourself
somewhere to go.

05:03.370 --> 05:05.939
I guess I probably shouldn't
have hid those love letters

05:05.939 --> 05:07.774
in her PSAT-prep
materials...

05:07.774 --> 05:09.676
[ Laughs ]
Hey, maybe they fell out.

05:09.676 --> 05:11.811
But if not,

05:11.811 --> 05:14.915
try to have some chill,
going forward, hmm?

05:14.915 --> 05:18.051
A little aloof
goes a long way.

05:18.051 --> 05:20.854
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

05:22.422 --> 05:26.126
♪♪

05:26.126 --> 05:27.594
♪ Yeah ♪

05:27.594 --> 05:29.963
♪♪

05:29.963 --> 05:32.299
[ Muffled giggling ]

05:32.299 --> 05:33.233
♪ Yeah ♪

05:33.233 --> 05:35.435
-I can't.
-It's kind of cute.

05:35.435 --> 05:39.639
♪♪

05:39.639 --> 05:41.174
Knock, knock!

05:41.174 --> 05:43.677
Lena! I thought we'd been over
the "knock-knock-enter."

05:43.677 --> 05:47.147
I'm sorry.
I'm so, so sorry.

05:47.147 --> 05:48.915
What are you
sorry for?

05:48.915 --> 05:51.885
Mom, can China sleep over?
No school tomorrow.

05:51.885 --> 05:53.553
Oh, honey.

05:53.553 --> 05:55.088
We...

05:55.088 --> 05:58.325
have to ask your dad
since it's almost his week.

05:58.325 --> 06:01.962
But since you asked
during mine,

06:01.962 --> 06:04.731
I guess I can answer.

06:06.032 --> 06:07.033
No.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.235
No? Why?

06:09.369 --> 06:11.338
Because I got an e-mail
from the school

06:11.338 --> 06:12.505
about strep throat.

06:12.505 --> 06:13.707
It's going around.

06:13.707 --> 06:15.108
So I think,
for health reasons,

06:15.108 --> 06:18.211
it would be better for you girls
to sleep separately.

06:18.211 --> 06:20.113
And also, remember
to wash your throats.

06:20.947 --> 06:22.148
Wash our throats?

06:22.148 --> 06:24.217
You also
may want to un-pretzel.

06:24.217 --> 06:28.121
Um, just 'cause I'm worried
about your circulation.

06:28.121 --> 06:30.423
It appears that your mom is
uncomfortable with intimacy.

06:30.423 --> 06:32.993
No, no. Not uncomfortable
with intimacy.

06:32.993 --> 06:34.594
Just a little confused.

06:34.594 --> 06:35.862
I'm confused, too.

06:35.862 --> 06:38.164
Because you said
that you "Stand by 'Q'."

06:38.164 --> 06:39.799
Remember? You were --
You were singing it.

06:39.799 --> 06:42.269
Really loudly.
While we were walking
upstairs.

06:42.269 --> 06:43.870
I did.
And I still do.

06:43.870 --> 06:45.605
In my defense, I don't know
the verses of that song,

06:45.605 --> 06:48.008
so it may have seemed
like more of an anthem
than I intended...

06:48.008 --> 06:50.543
-Lena.
-Mae.

06:50.543 --> 06:53.546
♪♪

06:53.546 --> 06:58.151
I guess I'm wondering
what the status is here.

06:58.151 --> 07:00.687
Should I mark you two as BFFs?
Or something more?

07:00.687 --> 07:03.323
I feel like we shouldn't have to
embrace a norm-core narrative

07:03.323 --> 07:06.526
just to make it easier for you
to comprehend, you know?

07:07.527 --> 07:09.195
Totally. Totally.

07:09.195 --> 07:12.866
It's just, as a parent,
it's my job to have rules.

07:12.866 --> 07:15.001
And the rules
may change

07:15.001 --> 07:16.903
if there are
feelings involved.

07:16.903 --> 07:19.039
Well, of course there are
feelings involved.

07:19.039 --> 07:21.041
♪ I don't want to be
your friend ♪

07:21.041 --> 07:23.076
♪ I want to kiss your lips ♪

07:23.076 --> 07:25.445
Did we answer
all your questions?

07:25.445 --> 07:26.946
♪ I want to kiss you ♪
If so, please leave.

07:26.946 --> 07:30.717
♪ Until I lose my breath ♪

07:30.717 --> 07:32.285
And close the door
on your way out.

07:32.285 --> 07:33.386
♪ I don't want to
be your friend ♪
[ Door opens ]

07:33.386 --> 07:35.655
♪ I want to kiss your lips ♪

07:35.655 --> 07:38.325
♪♪

07:38.325 --> 07:40.126
[ Whispering ] I think
Mae has a girlfriend.

07:40.126 --> 07:42.228
Also, what are you
still doing in here?

07:42.228 --> 07:44.097
[ Groggily ] I think
I fell asleep.

07:44.097 --> 07:46.800
Seriously? Gay Mae?

07:46.800 --> 07:48.168
Ooh.

07:48.168 --> 07:50.537
This is the most interested
I've ever been in her.

07:50.537 --> 07:51.871
Well, I'm all for it,

07:51.871 --> 07:54.641
but it's like Spoon-Plantation
in there.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.843
And now she wants her girlfriend
to sleep over.

07:56.843 --> 07:59.746
I fully expect my baby
to be a QUILTBAG.

07:59.746 --> 08:01.581
A what?
A QUILTBAG --

08:01.581 --> 08:02.816
Queer or questioning,

08:02.816 --> 08:04.217
undecided, intersex,

08:04.217 --> 08:06.219
lesbian, transsexual,
bisexual,

08:06.219 --> 08:08.588
allied/asexual,
genderqueer.

08:09.389 --> 08:12.092
Okay, I don't know which one
of those Mae is or isn't,

08:12.092 --> 08:14.327
but I need
to go talk to Martin.

08:14.327 --> 08:16.529
♪♪

08:16.529 --> 08:18.498
You know, you have
to leave at some point!

08:18.498 --> 08:22.469
♪♪

08:22.469 --> 08:23.536
Hey.
Martin: Hey.

08:23.536 --> 08:25.438
I'm making dinner,
if you're interested.

08:25.438 --> 08:27.474
"Nachos del Martino."

08:27.474 --> 08:30.043
The secret
is the tomatillos.

08:30.043 --> 08:31.978
[ Sniffs ]
They really level it up.

08:31.978 --> 08:35.482
No, thanks.
Listen, Mae has China over.

08:35.482 --> 08:37.150
Oh, that's fine.
There's plenty.

08:37.917 --> 08:41.020
Yeah, Martin,
this isn't nacho-related.

08:41.020 --> 08:44.157
I don't think China
should sleep over anymore.

08:44.157 --> 08:45.558
No school tomorrow.

08:45.558 --> 08:47.293
That's not the point.

08:47.293 --> 08:50.897
We wouldn't let Mason have
Bronwyn sleep over, right?

08:50.897 --> 08:52.732
Yeah, right,
but that's boy/girl.

08:52.732 --> 08:54.100
Mason is dating Bronwyn.

08:54.100 --> 08:55.702
Martin, what I'm trying
to tell you is --

08:55.702 --> 08:58.138
Dad, can China
sleep over?

08:58.138 --> 08:59.406
Wait, he's still "Dad"?

08:59.406 --> 09:02.509
Please? Neither of us
have strep.

09:02.509 --> 09:03.877
Both: Ahh.

09:03.877 --> 09:06.046
All right. I --
Well, I think it's...

09:06.046 --> 09:07.280
It's okay with me.

09:07.280 --> 09:09.616
Thank you, Daddy.
Love you.

09:09.616 --> 09:10.617
Cool system.

09:10.617 --> 09:11.918
You get a no,

09:11.918 --> 09:13.319
and then you just take it
to the higher court.

09:13.319 --> 09:14.554
Oh, I see.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.289
You girls don't have a problem
with male power

09:16.289 --> 09:18.124
when it works
in your favor.

09:19.059 --> 09:20.160
Why can't you
just back me up?

09:20.160 --> 09:21.594
What are you
worried about?

09:21.594 --> 09:25.031
I think that the two of them
are more than friends.

09:25.031 --> 09:27.167
And it makes sleeping over
more complicated.

09:27.167 --> 09:29.903
Why? They're both girls.
No one's getting pregnant.

09:29.903 --> 09:31.938
Okay, that's not
my only concern.

09:31.938 --> 09:34.074
Also, it's a huge
double standard.

09:34.074 --> 09:36.609
If we won't let Mason's
girlfriend sleep over,

09:36.609 --> 09:39.012
then the same boundaries
should apply to Mae.

09:39.012 --> 09:41.414
Boundaries, huh?

09:41.414 --> 09:42.715
If I recall,
someone's boundaries

09:42.715 --> 09:45.151
got a little bit blurry
the other night...

09:45.151 --> 09:47.153
Snaps were unsnapped.

09:47.153 --> 09:48.455
Or don't you remember?

09:48.455 --> 09:49.923
I remember...

09:49.923 --> 09:52.392
a portion of the events.
[ Laughs ]

09:52.392 --> 09:54.761
This is not about us,
Martin, all right?

09:54.761 --> 09:56.396
This is a big deal.

09:56.396 --> 09:58.498
And I know I'm supposed to just
disappear into the garage

09:58.498 --> 10:01.301
and let you tell me
all about it later, but...

10:01.301 --> 10:02.936
no, I don't want to do that.

10:02.936 --> 10:03.970
Not this week.

10:03.970 --> 10:05.205
Okay.

10:05.205 --> 10:06.339
So what are you
proposing exactly?

10:06.339 --> 10:07.807
I want to stay
in the house.

10:07.807 --> 10:09.676
And I want to navigate
this whole thing together,

10:09.676 --> 10:10.977
for better or worse.

10:10.977 --> 10:12.879
That's called marriage.

10:12.879 --> 10:13.913
You just
proposed marriage.

10:13.913 --> 10:15.081
No --
Just admit it.

10:15.081 --> 10:16.382
Don't hide behind
the kids.

10:16.382 --> 10:18.151
You made
a huge mistake.

10:18.151 --> 10:20.420
You want me back.
Bad.

10:20.420 --> 10:22.355
You are delusional.
Am I?

10:22.355 --> 10:24.557
You need to be more honest
about your feelings, Lena.

10:24.557 --> 10:26.059
And if you are
gonna propose,

10:26.059 --> 10:28.261
I'm gonna need you
to get down on one knee.

10:28.261 --> 10:29.596
I did it for you.

10:29.596 --> 10:32.465
You make your jokes,
fine, yeah.

10:32.465 --> 10:36.102
And then when this whole
Hormonal Chernobyl

10:36.102 --> 10:38.872
blows up in your face,
don't come crying to me.

10:38.872 --> 10:40.807
Hormonal Chernobyl?

10:40.807 --> 10:43.009
That is some
highly adept wordplay.

10:43.009 --> 10:45.745
I got to clap you out
for that one.

10:45.745 --> 10:46.946
Whoo!

10:46.946 --> 10:49.115
[ Mimics cheers ]

10:49.115 --> 10:50.116
[ Door closes ]

10:50.116 --> 10:51.551
[ Whistles ]

10:51.551 --> 10:52.552
♪♪

10:56.589 --> 10:57.924
♪ Baby, don't make me
spell it out for you ♪

10:57.924 --> 10:59.526
China: You have a psychotic
amount of nail polish.

10:59.526 --> 11:02.996
I feel like if we acknowledge
self-care as a privilege,

11:02.996 --> 11:04.697
then maybe it's okay?
[ Chuckles ]

11:04.697 --> 11:06.166
These pedicures
are a response

11:06.166 --> 11:08.368
to our institutional
lack of empathy.

11:08.368 --> 11:09.536
And your mother.

11:11.271 --> 11:12.572
Either of you
got a hot plate?

11:12.572 --> 11:13.740
Milo, get out.

11:13.740 --> 11:15.408
Okay, okay.

11:17.777 --> 11:19.412
It's almost impressive
how little your family

11:19.412 --> 11:21.614
respects the contract
of a closed door.

11:21.614 --> 11:23.149
I'm getting
a dead bolt.

11:23.149 --> 11:25.919
I'm telling you, man.
The tides are turning.

11:25.919 --> 11:27.320
The second they sense
you're not interested,

11:27.320 --> 11:29.455
they just start
throwing themselves at you.

11:29.455 --> 11:32.025
Hell-o! Sex with the ex
who wears specs?

11:32.025 --> 11:34.394
No, no, no.
No sex. No specs.

11:34.394 --> 11:35.395
But the other night,

11:35.395 --> 11:37.330
she put on
her bad-girl overalls.

11:37.330 --> 11:39.132
You know the ones where
you can almost see something...

11:39.132 --> 11:40.767
Osh Kosh M'Gosh!
[ Laughs ]

11:40.767 --> 11:42.936
[ Laughs ] Lena tried
to seduce me.

11:42.936 --> 11:44.537
And then tonight,
she tells me

11:44.537 --> 11:46.039
that she wants to move
into the house together

11:46.039 --> 11:48.541
to deal with some
"parenting issues."

11:48.541 --> 11:49.943
What parenting issues?

11:49.943 --> 11:53.046
[ Doorbell ringing ]

11:54.547 --> 11:56.616
Bronwyn.
Everything okay?

11:56.616 --> 11:58.351
No. Everything
not okay.

11:58.351 --> 11:59.652
Mason wasn't
returning my texts,

11:59.652 --> 12:01.154
so I took a screenshot
of my texts,

12:01.154 --> 12:03.056
three dots
and then nothing.

12:03.056 --> 12:06.192
What can I tell you?
He's a hard man to pin down.

12:06.192 --> 12:07.994
He's like the wind...

12:08.895 --> 12:10.830
Mason?
The middle boy?

12:10.830 --> 12:12.498
Mm-hmm.

12:14.701 --> 12:18.071
♪♪

12:18.071 --> 12:19.639
You see that?
What'd I say?

12:19.639 --> 12:22.108
I told Mason to gently apply
the cold shoulder,

12:22.108 --> 12:23.476
and here she is.

12:23.476 --> 12:24.644
Moth to flame.

12:24.644 --> 12:27.447
It's more like moth to
your teenage son's bedroom.

12:27.447 --> 12:28.915
Is that even allowed?

12:28.915 --> 12:31.384
[ Chuckles ] Mason won't even
get undressed in front of me.

12:31.384 --> 12:32.852
He showers
in board shorts.

12:32.852 --> 12:34.621
He shares a room
with his little brother.

12:34.621 --> 12:36.356
I think we're safe.

12:36.356 --> 12:37.724
You know what?

12:37.724 --> 12:39.158
I used to be a shy guy.

12:39.158 --> 12:40.727
I shared a room
with my grandparents,

12:40.727 --> 12:41.928
"Willy Wonka" style.

12:41.928 --> 12:44.597
And let me just say,
I made it work.

12:47.900 --> 12:49.636
What are you
doing down here, huh?

12:49.636 --> 12:52.505
You're supposed to be
upstairs protecting
your brother's virginity.

12:52.505 --> 12:54.440
I mean, do you want
to break up?

12:54.440 --> 12:56.209
Like, if so,
just say it.
No.

12:56.209 --> 12:58.144
That's the very last thing
on Earth I want.

12:58.144 --> 12:59.445
It's just, my dad thought

12:59.445 --> 13:01.014
that if I didn't have
more chill,

13:01.014 --> 13:02.415
I would scare you off.

13:02.415 --> 13:04.884
If I wanted chill,
I'd be dating Jake Tapper.

13:04.884 --> 13:07.453
But you? You're ardent
and unbolted.

13:07.453 --> 13:08.888
It's why ILY.

13:08.888 --> 13:10.957
You are seriously
gonna slay the PSATs.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.760
And I'd marry you
right now

13:13.760 --> 13:14.927
if it were legal.

13:14.927 --> 13:16.362
I'd marry you, too.

13:17.997 --> 13:19.565
I was saving myself,

13:19.565 --> 13:22.669
but since we're
theoretically engaged...

13:25.371 --> 13:28.141
Okay, let's get some fresh air
in here, shall we?

13:28.141 --> 13:29.976
Bronwyn, loving your level
of investment here,

13:29.976 --> 13:32.712
but you need to harness
all that energy into leaving.

13:32.712 --> 13:34.213
Hit the bricks, kid.
Yeah.

13:34.213 --> 13:36.449
So, my girlfriend
has to leave

13:36.449 --> 13:38.351
while Mae is on
a field trip to China?

13:38.351 --> 13:40.553
It's not
the same thing, Mason.
I know!

13:40.553 --> 13:42.655
Because Bronwyn and I
don't take baths together.

13:42.655 --> 13:46.359
♪♪

13:46.359 --> 13:47.694
You got to bounce, China.
That's it.

13:47.694 --> 13:50.396
Towel off and go home.
What's wrong with you?

13:50.396 --> 13:52.298
I want every door
on this floor open.

13:52.298 --> 13:53.633
I want all of you
to towel off.

13:53.633 --> 13:56.035
I'm not "toweling off"
with the door open.

13:56.035 --> 13:57.704
And I'm completely dry.

13:57.704 --> 13:59.505
Towel off!
All of you!

13:59.505 --> 14:00.873
You towel off!

14:00.873 --> 14:02.475
Your macho '90s advice

14:02.475 --> 14:04.410
almost ruined my relationship
with Bronwyn.

14:04.410 --> 14:05.778
Okay, slow down.

14:05.778 --> 14:08.114
There's no need
to take this out on the '90s.

14:08.114 --> 14:09.615
She doesn't like
mind games, Dad.

14:09.615 --> 14:12.685
You and I?
We are due for "the talk."

14:12.685 --> 14:14.320
And what about me?

14:14.320 --> 14:15.388
Exactly.

14:16.456 --> 14:18.324
That's what
we want to know.

14:19.292 --> 14:20.526
Hey, no, no, no, no.
D-Don't close it.

14:20.526 --> 14:22.695
Don't close it.
Don't close it!

14:22.695 --> 14:24.797
Mason. Mason. Mason!

14:24.797 --> 14:33.373
♪♪

14:33.373 --> 14:35.608
You were right.
It's crazy up there.

14:35.608 --> 14:37.510
There were closed doors,
there were locked lips,

14:37.510 --> 14:39.979
and kids in kimonos,
and Milo is...

14:39.979 --> 14:41.380
Do you have Milo?

14:41.380 --> 14:43.015
Oh, you know what?
I think I saw him earlier.

14:43.015 --> 14:44.684
Never mind.
Lena: I told you.

14:44.684 --> 14:46.052
They're really
teenagers now, Martin.

14:46.052 --> 14:47.487
It's scary.

14:47.487 --> 14:49.122
I know, but I thought
we were gonna side-step

14:49.122 --> 14:50.456
all this stuff.
Me, too.

14:50.456 --> 14:52.191
I thought it was gonna be
all, you know,

14:52.191 --> 14:54.026
fan-fic and Reddit threads
until college.

14:54.026 --> 14:56.028
But we're here.
Oh, we're here.

14:56.028 --> 14:58.498
And if we're too strict,
they'll rebel.
Yeah, and if we're too loose,

14:58.498 --> 15:01.033
they're gonna group bathe and
start trash-talking the '90s.

15:01.033 --> 15:02.502
I'm still so steamed.

15:02.502 --> 15:04.904
I'd always had such confidence
in our parenting skills --

15:04.904 --> 15:06.005
well, mine.

15:06.005 --> 15:07.507
But now according to Mae,

15:07.507 --> 15:10.943
I am labeling, objectifying,
and afraid of intimacy.

15:10.943 --> 15:15.148
Look, I don't want to go
back up there alone, okay?

15:15.148 --> 15:17.817
♪♪

15:17.817 --> 15:19.352
Will you take my hand

15:19.352 --> 15:21.053
in parenting
our horny children?

15:21.053 --> 15:22.922
♪♪

15:22.922 --> 15:24.157
I will.

15:24.157 --> 15:25.591
♪♪

15:30.396 --> 15:31.264
Mason: I'd feel a little
more comfortable

15:31.264 --> 15:33.199
talking privately

15:33.199 --> 15:34.467
with Mom.

15:34.467 --> 15:36.302
And I'm not loving
either of my options,

15:36.302 --> 15:37.670
but I prefer Dad.

15:38.771 --> 15:41.507
No. Well, th-that's not
how we're doing this.

15:41.507 --> 15:43.576
You both
have us both.

15:43.576 --> 15:46.045
From now on, you're not going
to get different answers

15:46.045 --> 15:47.446
on Mom Week
or Dad Week.

15:47.446 --> 15:49.415
We are going to have
house rules.

15:49.415 --> 15:50.783
And we're sticking
to them.

15:50.783 --> 15:53.586
No more playing both sides
against the middle.

15:53.586 --> 15:55.822
That said, we are very
interested in hearing

15:55.822 --> 15:58.391
what is working
and not working for you.
Yes.

15:58.391 --> 15:59.859
Okay, the floor
is now open.

15:59.859 --> 16:01.794
I am sick of sharing
a room with Milo.

16:01.794 --> 16:03.663
I want privacy
like Mae has.

16:03.663 --> 16:06.532
Me? I don't have privacy.
I want a lock on my door.

16:06.532 --> 16:07.934
I want a new mattress
in the garage.

16:07.934 --> 16:10.469
Please. I can't sleep
on the sofa bed anymore.

16:10.469 --> 16:12.038
Well, I want you
to try my nachos

16:12.038 --> 16:13.105
the next time I make them.

16:13.105 --> 16:14.106
They're really good.

16:14.106 --> 16:16.008
And I think
you'd be impressed.

16:16.008 --> 16:20.813
♪♪

16:20.813 --> 16:23.449
Well, I think
this is all doable.

16:23.449 --> 16:25.084
Especially
the nachos thing.

16:25.084 --> 16:27.186
Were you being serious?
Yes, I was.

16:28.554 --> 16:30.723
Look, you guys are clearly
at the age

16:30.723 --> 16:31.991
where you need
your privacy,

16:31.991 --> 16:33.326
and we want you
to have to have it.

16:33.326 --> 16:35.461
Because we trust you.

16:35.461 --> 16:37.763
So, on Mom
and Dad Weeks,

16:37.763 --> 16:39.799
your doors
can be closed.

16:39.799 --> 16:42.435
As long as the communication
is open.

16:42.435 --> 16:44.937
And Bronwyn's parents
are okay with it.

16:44.937 --> 16:47.273
And what about China?
Can she still sleep over?

16:48.207 --> 16:50.710
Unless she's your girlfriend,
and then she cannot.

16:50.710 --> 16:52.612
But we trust that
you will let us know

16:52.612 --> 16:55.181
when or if
that "label" applies.

16:55.181 --> 17:00.419
♪♪

17:00.419 --> 17:01.854
♪ Yeah ♪

17:03.456 --> 17:05.524
Nope.
What about my lock?

17:05.524 --> 17:07.326
Both: No locks.

17:07.326 --> 17:08.961
What about Milo?

17:08.961 --> 17:12.398
Oh, uh, your mom and I
talked about this.

17:12.398 --> 17:13.466
We're getting
rid of him.

17:13.466 --> 17:15.735
[ Laughter ]

17:15.735 --> 17:17.637
Seriously though,
where is Milo?

17:19.238 --> 17:20.940
I --

17:20.940 --> 17:23.409
Milo?

17:23.409 --> 17:24.410
Milo?

17:24.410 --> 17:27.346
♪♪

17:27.346 --> 17:29.081
Milo?
Are you in here?

17:29.081 --> 17:34.287
♪♪

17:34.287 --> 17:35.988
Oh, hello.

17:35.988 --> 17:39.525
Welcome to Milo Town.
Population one.

17:39.525 --> 17:41.093
We have
universal healthcare,

17:41.093 --> 17:43.696
free speech,
and no education.

17:44.497 --> 17:46.566
Pork and beans,
anyone?

17:46.566 --> 17:48.200
Um...

17:48.200 --> 17:50.002
Yeah,
I'll do a cup.

17:51.570 --> 17:54.574
Milo,
what is all this?

17:54.574 --> 17:58.978
Since everybody kept telling me
to get out of their rooms,

17:58.978 --> 18:01.047
I decided to strike out
on my own.

18:01.047 --> 18:05.151
Well, this is
wildly impressive.

18:05.151 --> 18:06.819
And these beans are...

18:06.819 --> 18:08.220
better than
they should be.

18:08.220 --> 18:10.923
Uh, but your mom
and I were thinking

18:10.923 --> 18:13.526
that the laundry room
holds a lot of potential

18:13.526 --> 18:15.428
for a young developer
like yourself.

18:15.428 --> 18:17.730
Let me take that
to the Mayor.

18:17.730 --> 18:20.232
[ Whispering indistinctly ]

18:20.232 --> 18:23.002
He's on board!

18:23.002 --> 18:24.537
Great.

18:24.537 --> 18:26.472
Okay, let's go,
Buttercup.

18:26.472 --> 18:28.774
♪♪

18:28.774 --> 18:30.609
[ Two knocks on door ]

18:30.609 --> 18:32.078
Hey.
Whoa!

18:32.078 --> 18:33.846
They weren't kidding about
that knock-knock-enter thing.

18:33.846 --> 18:36.983
You can't wait
for a "come in"?

18:36.983 --> 18:37.984
Sorry.

18:45.992 --> 18:51.564
♪♪

18:51.564 --> 18:52.865
[ Sweetly ]
Come in.

18:53.699 --> 18:55.167
Ha, ha.
[ Laughs ]

18:55.167 --> 18:56.969
I could've grown old
and died out there

18:56.969 --> 18:59.138
waiting for that
"come in."

18:59.138 --> 19:00.206
What's up?

19:00.206 --> 19:01.974
I'm proud of us.

19:01.974 --> 19:03.776
Yeah.

19:03.776 --> 19:05.845
What we did tonight,
that felt right.

19:05.845 --> 19:07.780
Safety in numbers,
I guess.

19:07.780 --> 19:10.149
I think
it's more than that.

19:10.149 --> 19:11.250
We're a good team.

19:11.250 --> 19:12.518
We are.

19:12.518 --> 19:14.186
Yeah.

19:14.186 --> 19:15.988
♪♪

19:15.988 --> 19:18.791
Can I ask you
a question?

19:18.791 --> 19:20.593
Do you think
I'm afraid of intimacy?

19:20.593 --> 19:23.129
♪♪

19:23.129 --> 19:25.564
Well, there's only one way
to know for sure...

19:25.564 --> 19:26.732
Stop it.

19:26.732 --> 19:28.000
To be clear,

19:28.000 --> 19:29.835
I'm not suggesting
we sleep together.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.937
I'm suggesting
we sleep together.

19:31.937 --> 19:33.706
You're suggesting
slumber.

19:33.706 --> 19:35.207
Correct.

19:35.207 --> 19:37.810
And I know how much you've been
nursing that heating pad,

19:37.810 --> 19:39.111
so come on.

19:42.114 --> 19:48.721
♪♪

19:48.721 --> 19:50.623
[ Both moan ]

19:50.623 --> 19:52.258
[ Both chuckle ]

19:52.258 --> 19:53.392
[ Sighs ]

19:53.392 --> 19:54.627
This is intimate.

19:54.627 --> 19:56.295
Mm.

19:56.295 --> 19:58.130
'Night.
'Night.

19:58.130 --> 19:59.732
♪♪

19:59.732 --> 20:02.134
[ Stomach gurgling ]

20:02.134 --> 20:04.303
Um...

20:04.303 --> 20:05.371
You know what?

20:05.371 --> 20:06.839
I shouldn't have eaten
those bathroom beans.

20:06.839 --> 20:08.240
It's a big mistake.

20:08.240 --> 20:11.143
The bed is all yours.
I'm gonna sleep in the garage.

20:11.143 --> 20:14.380
Wh-- There's, uh, ginger ale
in the mini-fridge.

20:14.380 --> 20:16.649
Take tiny sips!

20:16.649 --> 20:17.783
Oh.

20:17.783 --> 20:19.552
[ Sighs ]

20:19.552 --> 20:21.220
Feel better.

20:27.560 --> 20:29.562
[ Exhales sharply ]
Well, old boy. Take it sleazy.

20:29.562 --> 20:31.330
Quit being weird.

20:31.330 --> 20:32.865
I think
I got everything.

20:32.865 --> 20:35.534
Although, I was unable
to locate my booger box.

20:36.402 --> 20:38.270
Yeah, it is
what it sounds like.

20:38.270 --> 20:40.873
Basically just an old shoe box
full of my boogers.

20:40.873 --> 20:43.542
Anyway, if you find it,
it's yours.

20:43.542 --> 20:44.743
Thanks.

20:44.743 --> 20:46.345
Oh, speaking of boxes,

20:46.345 --> 20:49.749
I figured out a joint-custody
arrangement for our Xbox.

20:50.816 --> 20:52.618
So every other week,
we switch off.

20:52.618 --> 20:54.153
The Xbox goes between
my room and your room.

20:54.153 --> 20:56.856
And that way, even though
we don't live together,

20:56.856 --> 20:58.924
we can still get quality time
with our console.

20:58.924 --> 21:00.326
And on
your off weeks,

21:00.326 --> 21:02.962
you're still free
to play whatever you want.

21:02.962 --> 21:04.497
Works for
Mom and Dad.

21:04.497 --> 21:08.334
♪♪

21:08.334 --> 21:09.969
Yeah, you're right.
It's a stupid idea.

21:11.070 --> 21:14.073
I have a girlfriend now.
You can just have it.

21:14.073 --> 21:15.174
Yes!
